lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Revelations from former national security adviser John Bolton’s upcoming book are adding some drama to the ongoing Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump. Some reasons they could be important:
headline_main: Why It Matters: Bolton Revelations Complicate Trump Defense

abstract: Mr. Buttigieg is the star of the show at his campaign rallies in Iowa, where his crowds are virtually all white. In South Carolina, in front of black audiences, he still needs help telling his story.
snippet: Mr. Buttigieg is the star of the show at his campaign rallies in Iowa, where his crowds are virtually all white. In South Carolina, in front of black audiences, he still needs help telling his story.
lead_paragraph: WEST DES MOINES, Iowa — When Pete Buttigieg was asked Thursday if it worried him that mostly white people attended his big rallies in South Carolina, he said yes.

abstract: Career employees concluded that the way to lift the aid freeze was for someone to make a direct appeal to President Trump.
snippet: Career employees concluded that the way to lift the aid freeze was for someone to make a direct appeal to President Trump.
lead_paragraph: Given the extraordinary control that the White House has maintained over testimony and the release of emails, text messages and other documents by top Trump administration aides, there has been little evidence in the public domain to back up John Bolton’s claims that top White House advisers repeatedly pressed President Trump this summer to release his hold on the military aid to Ukraine.
headline_main: Bolton’s account corroborates now-public information on Ukraine aid freeze.

abstract: Senators hear the second installment of President Trump’s legal defense and arguments for why he should not be removed from office.
snippet: Senators hear the second installment of President Trump’s legal defense and arguments for why he should not be removed from office.
lead_paragraph: [Follow our live coverage and updates of the Trump Impeachment Trial vote.]

headline_main: Impeachment Trial Highlights: Trump’s Lawyers Avoid Bolton, Giuliani Surfaces and a History Lesson

abstract: Republican senators and officials attacked the former national security adviser after his manuscript leaked.
snippet: Republican senators and officials attacked the former national security adviser after his manuscript leaked.
lead_paragraph: For years, John R. Bolton has been a conservative Republican stalwart: foreign policy hawk, ambassador to the United Nations under President George W. Bush, fellow at the American Enterprise Institute, commentator on Fox News and national security adviser to President Trump.
headline_main: Republicans turn on Bolton as his account scrambles the impeachment trial.
